subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen:
Pale reddish brown, with abundant short recumbent setae. Male genitalia: Pygophore (
Fig. 12M, N
) rounded, anterior margin of dorsal aperture rounded, inner projections elongate, more pronounced posteriorly. Parameres with a tubercle at base of blade on outer surface (
Fig. 12O, P
). Aedeagus without spines; vesical lobes sclerotized; 
processus gonopori
long and slender.

